### 1. 🔒 Add Security Headers (`helmet`)
The app currently sends no security-hardening HTTP headers. An attacker can fingerprint the server and exploit missing protections like clickjacking or MIME-sniffing.

```js
const helmet = require('helmet');
app.use(helmet()); // Sets X-Frame-Options, X-Content-Type-Options, HSTS, CSP, etc.
